1
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,173
Bajalo. Get him down!

2
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:53,256
What have you got
against chickens?

3
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:55,342
One got choked last
night, thanks to you.

4
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:58,511
33-year-old male
with haemoptysis, fever.

5
00:02:58,595 --> 00:02:59,846
We can't even talk about it?

6
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:03,099
If you can't apologize, we
can't talk. And puncture wounds.

7
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,769
I'm not apologizing for
doing the right thing.

8
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:08,021
Lying to me was
not the right thing.

9
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:10,940
Puncture wounds are
from a crucifixion.

10
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:17,280
I lied to save
my patient's life.

11
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:19,699
I didn't lie to you,
I lied to my boss.

12
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:23,244
Either of those
arguments working yet?

13
00:03:25,789 --> 00:03:29,209
Guess that means I don't have
to go to the wedding on Saturday.

14
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,544
The hospital's
chairman of the board?

15
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:34,464
I'm not gonna stand him
up and neither are you.

16
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:37,425
I loathe weddings and their
seven levels of hypocrisy.

17
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:39,469
But you do seem awfully hissy,

18
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:42,847
and there's an outside chance
I can get you drunk and score.

19
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:45,171
So as long as you don't
take it as an admission of guilt,

20
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,394
sure, count me in.

21
00:03:47,685 --> 00:03:49,145
Bit too much honesty?

22
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:51,940
You're also going to the
rehearsal dinner Friday night.

23
00:03:52,982 --> 00:03:54,526
Dressy casual.

24
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,535
House-keeping.

25
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:07,789
Either you're crazy or you're
atoning for something naughty.

26
00:04:08,289 --> 00:04:09,582
And you're crazy.

27
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,543
He's a doctor.

28
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:13,253
I'm not atoning for anything.

29
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:15,255
That answers that, thanks.

30
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:19,801
My Marisa was diagnosed with terminal
brain cancer, stage IV glioblastoma.

31
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:22,554
When the doctors said
she had two months to live,

32
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,807
that's when I made my bargain.

33
00:04:26,182 --> 00:04:28,393
With your health
insurance carrier?

34
00:04:29,144 --> 00:04:30,353
With God.

35
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:31,478
Oh!

36
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:35,316
I told him I would nail myself to a
cross every year he kept her alive.

37
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,026
So how did that negotiation go?

38
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:39,904
You lowballed with ear
piercing and God countered?

39
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:44,242
Three weeks later, she was
cancer-free. That was four years ago.

40
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:46,744
Pontius Pilate,
misunderstood oncologist.

41
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:49,122
Yeah. My ex-wife
thinks I'm crazy, too.

42
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,916
She moved out the
first time I did this.

43
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,253
At least your daughter
has one viable role model.

44
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,338
- You don't believe in
God? - I did.

45
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,048
Then I grew my curly hairs.

46
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:01,694
So how do you think I was cured?

47
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,803
Maybe you were
misdiagnosed in the first place.

48
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:07,223
You have your answer,
Doctors. We have ours.

49
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:10,852
Causal determinism, we are
hardwired to need answers.

50
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:14,022
The caveman who heard
a rustle in the bushes

51
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,207
and checked out
to see what it was

52
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:17,609
lived longer than the guy who
assumed it was just a breeze.

53
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:19,152
The problem is,

54
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:21,988
when we don't find a logical
answer, we settle for a stupid one.

55
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,742
Ritual is what happens
when we run out of rational.

56
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:28,036
If you're done mocking him,
we need to prep for an LP.

57
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:31,873
Good. Another hole in him
should really make God's day.

58
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:40,006
Why are you late?

59
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:42,050
Your next dental
appointment isn't until January

60
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,469
and you just saw
your GP eight days ago.

61
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:47,430
Think stage IV glioblastoma
in an eight-year-old

62
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:48,848
can disappear in three weeks?

63
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,975
Had a flat tire.
Your patient has cancer?

64
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:53,228
Your tires have got less
than 5,000 miles on them.

65
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:55,813
No, and neither does
my patient's daughter.

66
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:58,566
I hit a piece of rebar
near a construction site.

67
00:05:59,234 --> 00:06:02,195
In three weeks?
It's highly unlikely.

68
00:06:02,278 --> 00:06:04,489
There's no construction site
between here and your home.

69
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:07,075
I agree, I think it was
a misdiagnosed cyst.

70
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,786
But there is one between
here and my dry cleaner.

71
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:13,998
It could be a misdiagnosis or it
could be spontaneous remission, but...

72
00:06:14,749 --> 00:06:16,751
Why would I lie about this?
I don't know yet.

73
00:06:16,834 --> 00:06:19,354
But you would've dropped off
your tie, it's got a mustard stain.

74
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:27,720
I was buying an engagement ring.

75
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:30,390
I'm gonna propose
to Sam at the wedding.

76
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:33,059
That is the second stupidest
thing I've heard today.

77
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:35,228
And I'm surprised
how close you came.

78
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:37,706
You didn't need to
buy her a new ring.

79
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,691
Isn't the first one good
for all-you-can-marry?

80
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:42,986
I assume you haven't
apologized to Cuddy yet.

81
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:44,487
Your stupidity
demands equal time.

82
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:46,197
Nothing to apologize for.

83
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,409
Pretend to apologize.

84
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:50,493
You want me to lie?

85
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:51,857
There's a lovely symmetry to it.

86
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,791
A lie got you into it,
a lie gets you out of it.

87
00:06:53,871 --> 00:06:56,583
Everybody lies.
I'm sure Cuddy...

88
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,546
Just need to give her a chance.

89
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:06,467
Yeah, that must've
been what I meant.

90
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,845
Have you seen the bride-to-be?

91
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,681
Gorgeous woman half
his age. He's a lucky guy.

92
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,349
Yeah.
For a while.

93
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,602
My father's 19 years
older than my mother

94
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:17,485
and they've been happily
married for 32 years.

95
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:20,398
I'm guessing your dad
wasn't on the Forbes 400

96
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:22,483
and your mom didn't
look like a swimsuit model.

97
00:07:24,068 --> 00:07:25,570
Sorry, that didn't
come out right.

98
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:30,533
My father was the classics chair at
Columbia and my mother was his student.

99
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:34,037
His gorgeous student.

100
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:37,165
What's it mean when somebody
takes their cell phone into the bathroom

101
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:38,408
when they're taking a shower?

102
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:42,795
Means they don't want you to
check their calls, e-mails or texts.

103
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,464
If we're talking
about your wife,

104
00:07:44,672 --> 00:07:47,717
it means the chickens
are coming home to roost.

105
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:51,095
Taub has been known to dabble.

106
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:52,263
Used to be.

107
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:56,434
Maybe it's just a habit. I do that
with my cell phone and I live alone.

108
00:07:56,517 --> 00:08:00,229
She has a meeting
today at 1:30, at a hotel.

109
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,649
I'm gonna go with
the chicken thing.

110
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:07,570
Negative for toxocara,
bacteroides, ascaris, everything.

111
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:10,531
So what looks like an infection
but doesn't test like one?

112
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,618
Animals.

113
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:15,261
I'm sure your wife's
just seeing a dude.

114
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:19,707
Patient works for Morgan
Timber Works, card's in the file.

115
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,377
"Specializing in stables,
barns and stalls."

116
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,462
He works around animals.
Rhodococcus equi.

117
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,422
Unless this guy's
sleeping in the manger.

118
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,925
Or has a history of open wounds.

119
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:39,727
We think you have rhodococcus
equi, a horse infection.

120
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:42,772
It's pretty rare in humans but
easily treatable with antibiotics.

121
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,440
Does it make your
teeth fall out?

122
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:45,525
No.

123
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:56,411
Then again, maybe we were wrong.

124
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:05,044
Fever, coughing up blood,
coughing up teeth.

125
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:10,675
Either God sweetened the deal
with a no-flossing clause, or...

126
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:12,135
Radiation sickness.

127
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,762
Yeah, maybe the carpenter
builds microwave ovens.

128
00:09:14,846 --> 00:09:15,888
Kaposi sarcoma?

129
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,390
No skin lesions.

130
00:09:17,473 --> 00:09:21,102
Heavy metal poisoning fits,
canned tuna, sushi, lead paint.

131
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:24,230
Heavy metal it is. Do a home
search and a peripheral smear.

132
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:26,941
I can't. I have a
personal errand to run.

133
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,610
Trying to catch
your wife cheating?

134
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:34,031
Why would you say that?

135
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:37,243
Missing mojo, posture
slumped, expression defeated,

136
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:40,329
you didn't try to back up your
theory. And Chase told me.

137
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:43,541
Go, find your mojo.

138
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:54,010
Shopkeeper,
I need a patient file.

139
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:55,469
Ask records.

140
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:56,679
Not one of our patients',

141
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:58,765
my patient's daughter.
Ask your patient.

142
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:00,892
He thinks I only want
it to debunk his faith.

143
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,643
And why would he think that?

144
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,730
Because he's strangely
perceptive for an idiot.

145
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:10,568
And I'm going to violate patient
privacy laws just to keep you happy?

146
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:14,739
You keep me happy, I return
the favor. Think of it as tat for tit.

147
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:18,659
When we're at work, we need
to focus on our work thoughts.

148
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,163
Why are you wearing that?

149
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:24,165
It's my dressy casual.
What do you think?

150
00:10:24,248 --> 00:10:26,083
You look like Wilson.

151
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:27,960
It looks weird.

152
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:30,129
But you knew I'd think that,

153
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:32,173
which makes me wonder
why you look disappointed.

154
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:34,342
If you prick me, do I not bleed?

155
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:40,681
You knew I wouldn't like it but
you thought I would say I did.

156
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:44,018
That's what this is about. You're
trying to trap me into lying to you.

157
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:46,437
You sure?
That sounds so juvenile.

158
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:55,363
You're okay with burglary now?

159
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:56,697
I asked his permission.

160
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:00,243
The reason we
don't ask permission

161
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:02,745
is we're afraid the patient
is going to hide something.

162
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:04,580
But our patient
hasn't been home,

163
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,374
lives alone,
doesn't have any help,

164
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,376
and has no motive
to hide anything.

165
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,670
You ask for his key, too?

166
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,296
Oh! Doesn't have one.

167
00:11:19,428 --> 00:11:21,264
And now we know why.

168
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:24,267
You think he's crazy?

169
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:27,687
Crucifixion's pretty convincing
evidence. Lead paint?

170
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,439
Place is too new.

171
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:33,150
He believes in a higher
power that can affect his life,

172
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,527
like most people on the planet.

173
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:37,655
True. On the other hand,
crucified himself.

174
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:41,617
No canned tuna and I don't
think we have to worry about sushi.

175
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:45,663
No computer, no television,
no music. What does he do?

176
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:49,166
He reads. Prayer has
been proven to aid recovery.

177
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,377
Only if the person knows
they're being prayed for.

178
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:54,547
Means there's no
objective effect.

179
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:58,843
So faith comes from within.
Not exactly a newsflash.

180
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:10,479
I guess worry is
good for the waistline.

181
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,405
It's not worry, it's starvation.

182
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:22,134
His tooth didn't fall out because
of heavy metal poisoning,

183
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,659
it fell out because
of malnutrition.

184
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:25,244
He does have rhodococcus equi.

185
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:27,121
Taub was right.

186
00:12:28,247 --> 00:12:30,666
He just didn't know why.

187
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:38,257
- It's locked!
- I'm busy.

188
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:40,426
I'll wait.

189
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,474
I really am busy.

190
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:48,601
Cuddy got me
the daughter's file.

191
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,770
Well, not Cuddy, exactly.
Her signature.

192
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,190
Well, not exactly her signature.

193
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,318
Another lie?

194
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:59,081
Thought you could
take a look at it for me.

195
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:01,113
Maybe you hadn't heard,
I'm kind of busy.

196
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,406
With what?

197
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,075
Sudoku.
What do you think?

198
00:13:04,241 --> 00:13:07,662
I'm the head of oncology
in a major hospital.

199
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:11,958
And yet these files are
not from this hospital.

200
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:16,462
These are from
Where-My-Fiancée-Works Memorial.

201
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:19,507
Sam's boss is doing a
clinical review of all of her files,

202
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:20,883
and she just wanted to make sure

203
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,928
everything's in order
before he starts on Monday.

204
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,721
Which explains why Sam
is too busy to look at my file.

205
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:29,141
If I don't help her, she can't
go to the wedding, and...

206
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,285
We fell in love at
her cousin's wedding,

207
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,688
which is why I want to
propose to her at a wedding.

208
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:35,982
And now, you have 60
seconds to berate me for that

209
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,734
and for helping my
girlfriend with her homework.

210
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:40,212
You don't want to
propose at a wedding.

211
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:42,655
Emotions running high,
people on edge.

212
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:47,076
You want to try somewhere like
a Buddhist temple or an aquarium,

213
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,662
or a Buddhist aquarium.

214
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:52,123
That only took 10 seconds.

215
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:54,709
You can spend the rest
of the time on my file.

216
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,424
Rachel?

217
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:16,856
Hey. How long
before you're home?

218
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:18,399
Not long.

219
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:22,570
Hey. Hey.

220
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:23,654
Uh...

221
00:14:24,739 --> 00:14:26,741
Yeah, you left your laptop on.

222
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:31,704
I saw you today, at the hotel.

223
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:34,165
Were you checking up on me?

224
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:36,375
Yes.

225
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,793
Satisfied?

226
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,254
Yes.

227
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:41,964
Good.

228
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,468
That's it?

229
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,470
You said you're
satisfied, that's enough.

230
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:51,640
You're not wondering
why it started,

231
00:14:52,058 --> 00:14:54,119
that makes me think you
don't want to talk about this,

232
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:55,394
which makes me think...

233
00:14:55,478 --> 00:14:56,979
You're being paranoid.

234
00:14:57,063 --> 00:14:59,231
You took your cell phone
with you into the bathroom

235
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:00,715
when you took
a shower this morning.

236
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:06,322
I made a new friend, online.

237
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,158
In a support group.

238
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,036
A guy?

239
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:13,162
Yes.

240
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:16,165
Support group for what?

241
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,502
For people with
unfaithful spouses.

242
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:27,384
Why didn't you tell us
you were starving yourself?

243
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,929
Well, I wasn't trying to.

244
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:33,015
I'm on a tight budget and
it seemed like an okay diet.

245
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,227
You seem to be feeling better.

246
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:38,979
Not really,
my legs are killing me.

247
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:45,569
