495
00:29:07,996 --> 00:29:08,997
Um...

496
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,876
I'm sorry about your daughter.

497
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,170
I never meant to hurt her.

498
00:29:16,671 --> 00:29:18,381
You just thought
she'd change my mind.

499
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:22,886
I was surprised she didn't.

500
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:26,514
So was I.

501
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:31,102
I didn't tell you the truth.

502
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:34,022
When I said I'm
not afraid to die.

503
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:37,359
But you're going
straight to heaven, so...

504
00:29:38,526 --> 00:29:41,237
That's what I believe.
But I'm human.

505
00:29:41,363 --> 00:29:43,531
So you know you may be wrong.

506
00:29:45,075 --> 00:29:47,535
How could you do
what you just did?

507
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:55,001
That's why we have beliefs, so
we can still see the right thing to do

508
00:29:55,085 --> 00:29:57,045
when we're blinded
with doubt and fear.

509
00:29:58,421 --> 00:30:03,134
Our beliefs define us. If
we lose them, who are we?

510
00:30:11,893 --> 00:30:15,563
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't
mean for it to go that way.

511
00:30:19,734 --> 00:30:23,655
You think I'm being
selfish but I'm not.

512
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:30,161
He makes me feel better
about me and about us.

513
00:30:31,162 --> 00:30:33,581
Well, that is hard to believe

514
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:38,420
because all I feel
right now is betrayed.

515
00:30:39,129 --> 00:30:40,255
I never wanted that.

516
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:41,339
Good.

517
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:45,844
Because just like you asked
me to stop my behavior,

518
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:48,304
I'm asking you to stop this.

519
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:53,685
No?

520
00:30:53,768 --> 00:30:55,437
I'm not gonna lie to you.

521
00:30:55,603 --> 00:30:57,272
Is this revenge?

522
00:30:58,815 --> 00:31:00,191
I don't know.

523
00:31:00,275 --> 00:31:02,986
But I do know that it's
something I need right now.

524
00:31:14,622 --> 00:31:15,957
What would you wear?

525
00:31:18,334 --> 00:31:20,045
I'm a sucker for the white gown.

526
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:25,884
Traditionally for young,
first-time brides.

527
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:29,637
Well, I may not be
young but I'd be first-time.

528
00:31:31,848 --> 00:31:34,309
That is a lie.

529
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:43,318
You were married before.
In 1987, for six days.

530
00:31:45,487 --> 00:31:47,847
Your knowledge of New Jersey
divorce law made me suspicious,

531
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:48,990
so I looked it up.

532
00:31:51,493 --> 00:31:53,036
So this was all your trap?

533
00:31:53,661 --> 00:31:57,248
Trap's primitive,
I prefer inveiglement.

534
00:31:57,332 --> 00:32:01,836
Anyway, the point is, I lied to
you, you lied to me, I forgive you.

535
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,386
Well played.

536
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:18,686
You're tired, aren't
you? All those files.

537
00:32:19,354 --> 00:32:22,524
No, no, I was thinking...

538
00:32:24,692 --> 00:32:27,487
I mean, if those two even have
the slightest chance of making it,

539
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:30,532
then we have to be a sure thing.

540
00:32:31,407 --> 00:32:33,701
And we've already
made all our mistakes.

541
00:32:34,536 --> 00:32:35,537
And...

542
00:32:41,709 --> 00:32:45,296
I've come to realize
that I love you

543
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:47,257
even more than I thought I did.

544
00:32:47,590 --> 00:32:50,718
Sam, will you marry me again?

545
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:58,393
Wow. I don't even
know what to say.

546
00:32:58,726 --> 00:33:00,145
I have a suggestion.

547
00:33:00,562 --> 00:33:03,231
Where did this even
come from? When did you...

548
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:08,361
You just came to realize?

549
00:33:08,444 --> 00:33:11,656
What made you love me even more?

550
00:33:12,949 --> 00:33:19,455
Everything you've done, your
work, your sense of morality.

551
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:24,085
The five cases.

552
00:33:24,919 --> 00:33:28,089
I not only agree with
what you did, I admire it.

553
00:33:28,256 --> 00:33:30,049
I didn't do anything.
You already asked me

554
00:33:30,133 --> 00:33:32,594
about the files and
I told you the truth.

555
00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:35,013
I know, and I get it.

556
00:33:36,306 --> 00:33:37,640
You don't believe me.

557
00:33:37,765 --> 00:33:42,020
I believe that you
are a wonderful person.

558
00:33:42,103 --> 00:33:43,354
Who lies and cheats.

559
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:44,439
No, Sam.

560
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:47,150
Listen, I'm on your side.

561
00:33:48,276 --> 00:33:50,028
I can't believe this.

562
00:33:52,488 --> 00:33:55,158
What? Sam. Sam,
don't do this.

563
00:34:21,017 --> 00:34:22,810
So how many do you think?

564
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:25,355
At least three.

565
00:34:26,231 --> 00:34:27,982
Hat-trick Chase.

566
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:32,862
See? Life of the bachelor.
All of the sex, none of the guilt.

567
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:37,325
It's not over, okay? I
just really miscalculated.

568
00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:40,411
I thought she'd forgiven
me for everything

569
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:44,999
but all those hurt feelings,
they never really went away.

570
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,921
That makes a lot more sense.

571
00:34:51,047 --> 00:34:54,550
Ignore him, he just got an idea.

572
00:34:56,719 --> 00:34:58,513
I have one more test to run.

573
00:35:02,392 --> 00:35:04,435
Uh, I hate weddings.

574
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:23,538
Won't be long now.

575
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:29,043
You'll be staring down the
yawning void before you know it.

576
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:31,587
You came from a
wedding to tell me that?

577
00:35:31,713 --> 00:35:36,718
No, I came from a
wedding to run a PET scan.

578
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:38,553
Thought you'd given up on me.

579
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,889
I have. PET scan
was for your daughter.

580
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:44,309
I was wrong about her.

581
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,729
She did have glioblastoma.

582
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:53,443
And she still does.
Cancer never went away.

583
00:35:54,569 --> 00:35:57,989
Yes, it did. They
tested her every year.

584
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,824
With a CT scan

585
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:04,329
which misses all the tiny little
tumors that a PET scan doesn't.

586
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:08,416
You made a mistake. She
does not have cancer anymore.

587
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:11,502
I ran it twice, no mistake.

588
00:36:15,256 --> 00:36:17,091
Looks like God broke your deal.

589
00:36:20,762 --> 00:36:22,263
I'm sorry.

590
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:25,516
But I'm also right.

591
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:31,522
You're a bastard.

592
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:39,655
Do whatever you want to me.

593
00:36:41,449 --> 00:36:42,825
Good call.

594
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:52,251
Surprised you've got enough
strength to come to work today.

595
00:36:52,335 --> 00:36:55,129
Thirty-six hours is long
enough for me to recover.

596
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:57,840
And not nearly long enough
for this guy to be getting better.

597
00:36:57,965 --> 00:37:00,718
House wanted us checking
every 12 hours anyway.

598
00:37:01,636 --> 00:37:02,678
Sorry I took off on you.

599
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:04,472
Twice.

600
00:37:04,972 --> 00:37:07,558
First one was my bad.
Second one I had no choice.

601
00:37:08,810 --> 00:37:10,061
It was a threesome.

602
00:37:11,479 --> 00:37:12,814
They're overrated.

603
00:37:13,981 --> 00:37:15,733
He's bluffing.
He's bluffing.

604
00:37:17,568 --> 00:37:18,986
Get House.

605
00:37:20,405 --> 00:37:23,741
Got something to show you.
Your daughter's PET scan.

606
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:26,577
It's clean.

607
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:28,871
She's fine.

608
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:31,666
My bad.

609
00:37:32,208 --> 00:37:34,377
Got her mixed up
with Marion Silver.

610
00:37:35,002 --> 00:37:38,589
Marisa Silva.
That's believable, right?

611
00:37:39,382 --> 00:37:42,927
Anyhow, good news for
you, bad news for Mr. Silver.

612
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:46,848
You tricked me. God
didn't break our deal, I did.

613
00:37:48,057 --> 00:37:51,060
You led me into
temptation and I followed.

614
00:37:51,185 --> 00:37:52,937
And God will
punish you for that.

615
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,939
He has to.
'Cause if he didn't,

616
00:37:55,189 --> 00:37:56,774
it'd make you wonder,
wouldn't it?

617
00:37:56,858 --> 00:37:58,025
He will.

618
00:37:58,401 --> 00:38:01,612
Well, that's why I'm
so confused by this.

619
00:38:02,697 --> 00:38:06,284
This is your MRI. Shows
incremental improvement.

620
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:07,535
You're getting better.

621
00:38:09,203 --> 00:38:10,683
I double-checked
the name on this one.

622
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:16,210
But it's not all good news.
This patient is screwed.

623
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:19,589
Technical term is
dead as a doornail.

624
00:38:20,047 --> 00:38:21,132
Who is that?

625
00:38:21,424 --> 00:38:22,467
God.

626
00:38:23,259 --> 00:38:24,844
You broke your deal with him

627
00:38:24,927 --> 00:38:26,864
but your daughter's fine
and you're getting better.

628
00:38:26,888 --> 00:38:30,391
Nothing bad happened.
Which can only mean one thing,

629
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:31,809
there is no God.

630
00:38:33,102 --> 00:38:35,855
'Course, if your daughter
gets hit by a meteorite today,

631
00:38:35,938 --> 00:38:38,107
I would have some
serious egg on my face.

632
00:38:40,234 --> 00:38:43,738
You're smiling. I assume
that means you're miserable.

633
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:46,324
It means I'm happy.

634
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:50,703
This doesn't mean
God doesn't exist,

635
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:53,331
it just means
he's truly merciful.

636
00:38:55,082 --> 00:38:56,918
My beautiful Marisa was right,

637
00:38:57,835 --> 00:38:59,128
God is all about love.

638
00:38:59,253 --> 00:39:02,924
Punishment is proof of God and
no punishment is proof of God.

639
00:39:03,925 --> 00:39:05,676
Ingenious argument.

640
00:39:07,595 --> 00:39:09,263
Faith isn't an argument.

641
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,519
I'd like to see my daughter.

642
00:39:24,111 --> 00:39:25,863
Everyone else knew?

643
00:39:26,531 --> 00:39:29,492
Everyone I could trust.
So, yes.

644
00:39:31,118 --> 00:39:33,788
If you had told me,
he'd be dead by now.

645
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:37,041
So why do I still
want to tell the truth?

646
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:41,504
Either you're naive, or you have
scruples. I'm not sure which is worse.

647
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:45,299
This is insane.
We can't work like this.

648
00:39:46,509 --> 00:39:47,718
I can.

649
00:39:53,975 --> 00:39:54,976
Sam?

650
00:39:56,143 --> 00:39:58,688
Sorry, I was hoping to be
done before you got home.

651
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,649
We had a fight.
We had one fight.

652
00:40:02,483 --> 00:40:04,777
And I admitted I was wrong.

653
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:06,460
We can talk about it,
we can get over it.

654
00:40:06,487 --> 00:40:07,530
This is about trust.

655
00:40:07,655 --> 00:40:09,949
I never lied to
you about anything.

656
00:40:10,032 --> 00:40:12,660
I know,
and I always trusted you.

657
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:14,245
I...

658
00:40:15,162 --> 00:40:16,914
Maybe we could
talk to a counselor.

659
00:40:16,998 --> 00:40:18,708
You said that helped
after our divorce.

660
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:21,502
It did, and I think
I changed a lot.

661
00:40:22,003 --> 00:40:25,006
And I haven't.
This is my fault?

662
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:28,759
I know where this is going.

663
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:30,386
And I don't want
to go there again.

664
00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:37,435
You're quitting, Sam.
You're quitting again.

665
00:40:38,894 --> 00:40:40,688
So I guess you haven't
changed that much.

666
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:11,052
Good work today.

667
00:41:12,136 --> 00:41:13,971
Don't even think your
patient's gonna sue.

668
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:17,266
Looks like everybody's happy.

669
00:41:21,937 --> 00:41:23,481
I've been an idiot.

670
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:27,860
I got this argument
stuck in my head.

671
00:41:27,943 --> 00:41:32,239
If everybody lies, then trust is
not only unfounded and pointless,

672
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:34,241
it's fictional.

673
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:38,579
But trust is not an argument
that can be won or lost.

674
00:41:38,954 --> 00:41:44,168
Maybe I just have to suspend
my cynicism and believe.

675
00:41:46,253 --> 00:41:48,297
Maybe it's time
I took a leap of faith.

676
00:41:52,593 --> 00:41:53,969
I'm sorry.

677
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:56,931
I won't lie to you again.

678
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:00,810
Thank you.

679
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:17,952
Sam left me.

680
00:42:18,327 --> 00:42:19,954
What a moron.

681
00:42:21,831 --> 00:42:23,791
Too soon. I'm still
in love with her.

682
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:26,293
I meant you.

683
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:30,297
Do you have a drink?
Or drinks?

684
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:32,174
Cuddy's coming over.

685
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:39,056
Does she know you're here?

686
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:42,393
I apologized to her.

687
00:42:47,857 --> 00:42:50,317
Good for you.

688
00:42:53,028 --> 00:42:56,198
Not really, I lied.

689
00:43:00,327 --> 00:43:03,831
I just took your advice.
Too bad you didn't.

690
00:43:07,501 --> 00:43:09,003
Good for you.

